comments: Sochan (SAS) moves alongside Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) path and maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt.
Wembanyama (SAS) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal lower body contact occurs with Jackson Jr. (MEM) after the release.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) grasps and then quickly releases Wembanyama's (SAS) jersey off-ball.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) initiates contact with Wembanyama's (SAS) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Jones (SAS) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects it away from Pippen Jr. (MEM) during the steal.
Pippen Jr. (MEM) briefly grasps and immediately releases Jones Jr.'s (SAS) jersey as marginal contact occurs when he starts his dribble.
Johnson (SAS) wraps his arm around LaRavia's (MEM) back as his hand slides off the ball onto LaRavia's arm, which affects LaRavia's SQBR.
Jackson (MEM) is not vertical when he initiates illegal contact with Johnson's (SAS) arm, affecting Johnson's play at the basket.

Replay review of the foul called on Pippen Jr. (MEM) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Pippen Jr. makes illegal contact with both Johnson's (SAS) head and arm during his contest of the shot at the basket.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) establishes a slightly wide screening position in Jones' (SAS) path and marginal lower body contact occurs during the pick.

Jackson Jr. (MEM) legally contests Vassell's (SAS) jump shot attempt. Any marginal follow-through contact as they return to the ground is a result of Vassell extending his leg and leaning forward into Jackson Jr. to ensure there is contact.
Aldama (MEM) blocks Sochan's (SAS) shot attempt at the basket and any contact to his hand is incidental.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of offensive goaltending on Wembanyama (SAS) is confirmed.  Wembanyama makes contact with the ball while it is still in the imaginary cylinder above the rim.

Sochan (SAS) and Johnson (SAS) make clean contact with the ball to deflect the rebound away from Jackson Jr. (MEM). After the deflection, any follow-through contact between LaRavia (MEM) and Johnson as they pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
LaRavia (MEM) touches the ball last before it bounces on the baseline out of bounds. Possession is correctly maintained by the Spurs.
Jackson (MEM) briefly engages and immediately disengages with Vassell (SAS) as marginal contact occurs when the screen is set.
Sochan (SAS) releases the pass and incidental lower-body contact occurs with Pippen Jr. (MEM) as they come together at the end of the drive.
Sochan (SAS) moves alongside Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) path and maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
During the inbound, Jackson (MEM) immediately slides his hand off of Vassell's (SAS) body and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) legally contests Wembanyama's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
